The President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), on Monday night, met with a leader of the ruling All Progressives Congress, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu. Tinubu was accompanied to the meeting by a former national chairman of the APC, Chief Bisi Akande. The meeting was held inside the President’s official residence inside the Presidential Villa, Abuja. Buhari also met behind closed doors with the Borno State Governor, Prof Babagana Zulum. The meeting was said to have centred on the security situation in the state. Details later…